{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/superficial-vein-thrombosis-superficial-thrombophlebitis/background-information/definition/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"63f70d2c-b895-556e-8108-242a922f573d","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 7df3eed4-cf4d-4a25-b093-92d829255b0e --><h2>What is it?</h2><!-- end field 7df3eed4-cf4d-4a25-b093-92d829255b0e -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 0f4ec841-54e0-485e-b8ef-ec7a7ced74ce --><!-- begin field bb71f998-80c3-4fe8-96a1-da9a06cfebd2 --><ul><li><strong>Superficial vein thrombosis (also known as superficial thrombophlebitis) </strong>results from thrombus formation in a superficial vein, with associated inflammation in the tissue surrounding the vein [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/superficial-vein-thrombosis-superficial-thrombophlebitis/references/\">BMJ, 2015</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/superficial-vein-thrombosis-superficial-thrombophlebitis/references/\">BMJ, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/superficial-vein-thrombosis-superficial-thrombophlebitis/references/\">Di Nisio, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/superficial-vein-thrombosis-superficial-thrombophlebitis/references/\">Thrombosis Canada, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/superficial-vein-thrombosis-superficial-thrombophlebitis/references/\">Almeida, 2019</a>].<ul><li>It most commonly occurs in the saphenous vein and its tributaries of the lower limbs (60–80% of cases) [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/superficial-vein-thrombosis-superficial-thrombophlebitis/references/\">BMJ, 2015</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/superficial-vein-thrombosis-superficial-thrombophlebitis/references/\">BMJ, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/superficial-vein-thrombosis-superficial-thrombophlebitis/references/\">Thrombosis Canada, 2018</a>]. Superficial veins in other areas of the body (for example the upper limbs, neck, abdominal wall, breasts, or arms) can also be affected [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/superficial-vein-thrombosis-superficial-thrombophlebitis/references/\">Scott, 2015</a>] but are outside the scope of this CKS topic.</li><li>Thrombus formation may be idiopathic or associated with one or more <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/superficial-vein-thrombosis-superficial-thrombophlebitis/background-information/causes-risk-factors/\">risk factors</a>.  </li></ul></li><li><strong>Migratory thrombophlebitis </strong>is thrombophlebitis that recurs at varying sites but most commonly in the leg. It is often associated with a serious underlying cause, such as cancer [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/superficial-vein-thrombosis-superficial-thrombophlebitis/references/\">BMJ, 2018</a>].<ul><li>Trousseau syndrome is a rare condition characterized by recurrent and migratory superficial vein thrombosis, frequently in unusual sites, such as the arm or chest (also called Mondor's disease when involving chest wall veins). It is most often associated with gliomas and adenocarcinomas of the gastrointestinal tract (stomach, pancreas, and colon), lungs, breasts, ovaries, and prostate. It can also be seen with Behcet's and Buerger's disease [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/superficial-vein-thrombosis-superficial-thrombophlebitis/references/\">BMJ, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/superficial-vein-thrombosis-superficial-thrombophlebitis/references/\">Almeida, 2019</a>]. </li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field bb71f998-80c3-4fe8-96a1-da9a06cfebd2 --><!-- end item 0f4ec841-54e0-485e-b8ef-ec7a7ced74ce -->","topic":{"id":"07820562-ab2f-5ea0-9097-3e6e5a62bec4","topicId":"3c0e3637-8623-4aa4-9bdf-83c4ead61135","topicName":"Superficial vein thrombosis (superficial thrombophlebitis)","slug":"superficial-vein-thrombosis-superficial-thrombophlebitis","lastRevised":"Last revised in March 2020","chapters":[{"id":"a5f3a42e-3e23-59d7-83fb-fd26995ebf74","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"1ceec510-5b3b-59b2-be08-fde928defc1e","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"8b0cc395-7b80-5e19-a891-b27b1d88c9f3","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"75c7c081-3b2a-5f62-aead-766ba5534a36","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"fcc6e0b2-bfab-56d2-a1e0-57e5f3f6c19a","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"6da7aa90-c506-5e57-baed-74b22c09af0a","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"8a802f98-487d-5c7e-829e-4a9e669fe875","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"7dff5216-bc4a-529e-854f-a128cb8b54ca","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"999e411a-0346-5c64-aa2d-eba133633715","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"fed9fa0e-2eb0-5385-b244-1efe9fad43ce","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"58585f51-d63a-5cf7-bd5e-f14b6dd9c02a","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"62ad8730-5197-5854-acff-ffd86c7f8b92","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"5d82d4b3-7ef8-52e7-a668-a65cc11d7bf7","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"63f70d2c-b895-556e-8108-242a922f573d","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Defi